# Airbnb Listings Demo Page

A simple client-side app that loads and displays the first **50** Airbnb-style listings via **AJAX (fetch + await)** and renders each card with:

- Listing **name**
- **Description**
- **Amenities**
- **Host** (name + photo, with “Superhost” badge)
- **Price**
- **Thumbnail**
- **Creative addition**: 
  - 🔎 Live **search** (filters by title/description/amenities/host)
  - ⭐ **Favorites** (persisted in `localStorage`)

> **Live demo:** **[https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/YOUR_REPO_NAME](https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/YOUR_REPO_NAME)**  
> *(Replace with your actual deployment URL once GitHub Pages is enabled.)*

---

## 📁 Project Structure
├── index.html
├── about.html
├── css/
│ └── main.css
├── js/
│ └── main.js
├── package.json ← houses the "listings" array (data source)
└── package-lock.json

### Data Source (No extra files required)
Instead of a separate `data/*.json`, this project reads listings from **`package.json`** under a top-level `"listings"` array.  
This keeps your current file names unchanged, per the assignment constraints we discussed.

`main.js` tries `./package.json` first (then `./package-lock.json`), reads `json.listings`, and renders the **first 50**.

---

## 🚀 How to Run Locally

Because browsers block `fetch()` from `file://`, run a local server:

**VS Code Live Server**
1. Install the *Live Server* extension.
2. Right-click `index.html` → **Open with Live Server**.

